          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Ceasefire call</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/putin-trump-ceasefire-call.png" alt="Russian President Vladimir Putin and U.S. President Donald Trump in a public setting." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Trump and Putin at a public event amid discussions on the ceasefire. Credits: AlJazeera
          </i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">During a call with Trump, President Putin agreed to a partial 30-day ceasefire on energy infrastructure attacks with Ukraine. While the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-h1-1-white-house-welcomed-the-news" target="_blank">White House welcomed the news</a>, it fell short of the complete ceasefire Ukraine had agreed to. However, negotiations are still open for a broader deal to end the conflict. Further negotiations for a maritime ceasefire in the Black Sea, a complete ceasefire, and permanent peace will occur.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">While the ceasefire protects the energy infrastructure, the loophole in the agreement can be exploited to attack ports, bridges, and other Ukrainian infrastructure. Putin mentioned that a “key condition” for a complete ceasefire includes halting all foreign military aid to Ukraine and suspending Western intelligence sharing with Kyiv. Additionally, Putin informed Trump of a planned prisoner exchange of 175 Russian and 175 Ukrainian prisoners. 
       </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said he would contact Trump to understand what the US and Russia offered each other. He also added that Russia could show its seriousness about peace talks by freeing all prisoners. The call between Trump and Putin followed a recent agreement between US and Ukrainian officials for a monthlong ceasefire proposal. 

</p>
        </mj-text>
