        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Ex-Georgian President jailed </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/mikheil-saakashvili-georgia-court-sentencing.png" alt="Former Georgian President Mikheil Saakashvili speaking at a rally with Georgian and European Union flags in the background." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Mikheil Saakashvili speaking at a rally in front of the Georgian Parliament. Credits: Mariam Nikuradze/OC Media.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">A Georgian court sentenced former President Mikheil Saakashvili to an additional four and a half years in prison for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-h2-2-illegally-crossing-the-border" target="_blank">illegally crossing the border</a>, bringing his total sentence to 12 and a half years. Last week, a nine-year sentence was handed down for misusing public funds during his presidency. Saakashvili denounced his ongoing prosecution as politically motivated. 
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Saakashvili returned to Georgia from exile in 2021. He now holds Ukrainian nationality instead of Georgian. Saakashvili has been jailed on multiple charges, including abuse of power. He argues that the charges are designed to prevent him from challenging the current government led by the Georgian Dream party and accused the Georgian authorities of using the judicial system to silence political opponents.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The EU and various human rights organizations have raised concerns over his treatment and called for his release and proper medical care. Saakashvili is a very polarizing figure known for his pro-Western policies and public sector reform in Georgia. He was also President during the Russian-Georgian War in 2008. He accuses the government of punishing him for opposing Russian influence in Georgia.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
