        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">South African ambassador kicked out</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The US declared South Africa’s Ambassador Ebrahim Rasool persona non grata over comments he made about America’s racial demographics.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The US State Department has declared South Africa’s Ambassador to the US, Ebrahim Rasool, a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-h3-3-persona-non-grata" target="_blank">persona non grata</a>. He has been ordered to leave the country by Friday. Secretary of State Marco Rubio’s social media post accusing Rasool of being a “race-baiting politician” who dislikes President Trump. He referred to comments Rasool made during a South African webinar about America’s racial demographics. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The US formally notified South Africa’s embassy, stating Rasool’s diplomatic immunity expired Monday. South Africa expressed concern over learning the decision from social media before official communication and plans to raise the issue with the US diplomatically. South African President Cyril Ramaphosa said the situation is a minor setback and still vowed commitment to rebuilding relations with the US.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The move comes amid strained ties, as the Trump administration recently halted funding to South Africa. The administration has been accusing the South African government of pushing anti-white policies and supporting groups like Hamas and Iran. South African President Cyril Ramaphosa said the relationship with the United States will be put on an even keel and urged people not to have sleepless nights.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
