          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇮🇳 Nagpur sees violent clashes at Mughal emperor's tomb</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Violent clashes erupted in Nagpur in central India over the tomb of 17th-century Mughal emperor Aurangzeb. There were around a dozen injuries and significant property damage. Hindu nationalist group Vishva Hindu Parishad (VHP) staged protests demanding the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-br1-4-removal-of-the-tomb" target="_blank">removal of the tomb</a>. The group cites Aurangzeb's controversial legacy among Hindus. At least 50 people were arrested, and local authorities imposed a curfew. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The VHP belongs to the same family of organizations as Prime Minister Narendra Modi's Bharatiya Janata Party. His government has been accused of discriminating against India's  Muslim minority. Previously, Modi has accused the Mughal ruler of trampling on the Hindu faith and persecuting its followers. Devendra Fadnavis, the chief minister, expressed some support for removing the tomb while condemning the violence. </p>
        </mj-text>
