          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇭🇺 Hungary bans Pride events and allows the use of facial recognition software</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hungary’s parliament passed a law to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-br2-5-ban-pride-events" target="_blank">ban pride events</a>, including the Budapest Pride march, and allow facial recognition software to identify attendees. The bill targets events violating Hungary’s 2021 "child protection" law. The law prohibits the "depiction or promotion" of LGBTQ+ content to minors. Attendees could face fines of up to roughly $550.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">PM Viktor Orbán's government runs on a platform that promotes traditional family values. It presents the law as a way to protect children from “sexual propaganda.” Critics, including Pride organizers, argue the bill restricts freedom of speech and assembly. They also argue that this is political theater and they have more important priorities to address. Hungarian opposition members lit smoke bombs in the parliament to protest the new law.</p>
        </mj-text>
