          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What happened in the 2008 Russo-Georgian war?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/russo-georgian-war-2008-map.png" alt="A map highlighting Russia and Georgia, illustrating their geographical positions. 2008 Russo-Georgian war,." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Map showing Russia and Georgia, highlighting their geographical positions in the context of the 2008 Russo-Georgian War.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">​​The Russo-Georgian War occurred in August 2008, on the first day of the Beijing Olympics. The war centered around the regions of South Ossetia and Abkhazia, both of which had declared independence from Georgia in the early 1990s after the collapse of the Soviet Union. Russia supported both regions as people obtained Russian nationality due to Russia’s <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-03-2025-f1-6-passportization" target="_blank">passportization</a> practices.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Russia took advantage of Georgia’s wish to reclaim control of the area. The war began when Georgia tried to regain control of South Ossetia. Russia sent large military forces into South Ossetia, quickly advancing into Georgia and launching airstrikes. Fighting also spread to the Abkhazia region. Russia's intervention led to widespread destruction and civilian casualties.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Despite the international community's hesitance, Russia also recognized South Ossetia and Abkhazia as independent republics. The conflict lasted for five days and ended with a ceasefire brokered by the French presidency of the European Union. The war caused a shift in Georgia’s foreign policy as it moved closer to the West while Russia cemented its influence in the separatist regions.</p>
          
